CA1050.fullDescription: Types are declared in namespaces to prevent name collisions and as a way to organize related types in an object hierarchy.

CA1860.fullDescription: Prefer using 'IsEmpty', 'Count' or 'Length' properties whichever available, rather than calling 'Enumerable.Any()'. The intent is clearer and it is more performant than using 'Enumerable.Any()' extension method.

CS0168.shortDescription: Variable is declared but never used

CS8618.shortDescription: Non-nullable field must contain a non-null value when exiting constructor. Consider adding the 'required' modifier or declaring as nullable.

S1118.shortDescription: Utility classes should not have public constructors
S1118.fullDescription: Whenever there are portions of code that are duplicated and do not depend on the state of their container class, they can be centralized inside a "utility class". A utility class is a class that only has static members, hence it should not be instantiated.

S1192.shortDescription: String literals should not be duplicated
S1192.fullDescription: Duplicated string literals make the process of refactoring complex and error-prone, as any change would need to be propagated on all occurrences.

S1199.shortDescription: Nested code blocks should not be used
S1199.fullDescription: Nested code blocks create new scopes where variables declared within are inaccessible from the outside, and their lifespan ends with the block.

S125.shortDescription: Sections of code should not be commented out
S125.fullDescription: Commented-out code distracts the focus from the actual executed code. It creates a noise that increases maintenance code. And because it is never executed, it quickly becomes out of date and invalid.

S1643.shortDescription: Strings should not be concatenated using '+' in a loop
S1643.fullDescription: StringBuilder is more efficient than string concatenation, especially when the operator is repeated over and over as in loops.

S2629.fullDescription: Logging arguments should not require evaluation in order to avoid unnecessary performance overhead. When passing concatenated strings or string interpolations directly into a logging method, the evaluation of these expressions occurs every time the logging method is called, regardless of the log level. This can lead to inefficient code execution and increased resource consumption.

S3903.shortDescription: Types should be defined in named namespaces
S3903.fullDescription: Types are declared in namespaces in order to prevent name collisions and as a way to organize them into the object hierarchy. Types that are defined outside any named namespace are in a global namespace that cannot be referenced in code.

S4136.shortDescription: Method overloads should be grouped together
S4136.fullDescription: For clarity, all overloads of the same method should be grouped together. That lets both users and maintainers quickly understand all the current available options.

S5122.shortDescription: Having a permissive Cross-Origin Resource Sharing policy is security-sensitive
S5122.fullDescription: Having a permissive Cross-Origin Resource Sharing policy is security-sensitive. It has led in the past to the following vulnerabilities:

S6667.shortDescription: Logging in a catch clause should pass the caught exception as a parameter.
S6667.fullDescription: This rule raises an issue on logging calls inside a catch clause that does not pass the raised Exception.

S6960.shortDescription: Controllers should not have mixed responsibilities
S6960.fullDescription: ASP.NET controllers should not have mixed responsibilities. Following the Single Responsibility Principle (SRP), they should be kept lean and focused on a single, separate concern. In short, they should have a single reason to change.

S6967.shortDescription: ModelState.IsValid should be called in controller actions
S6967.fullDescription: In the context of ASP.NET Core MVC web applications, both model binding and model validation are processes that take place prior to the execution of a controller action. It is imperative for the application to examine the ModelState.IsValid and respond accordingly.

S6968.shortDescription: Actions that return a value should be annotated with ProducesResponseTypeAttribute containing the return type
S6968.fullDescription: In an ASP.NET Core Web API, controller actions can optionally return a result value. If a controller action returns a value in the happy path, for example ControllerBase.Ok(Object), annotating the action with one of the [ProducesResponseType] overloads that describe the type is recommended.
